  • java.lang.Object
    • preibisch_imagelib2.view.composite.AbstractComposite<T>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, NumericType<C>, Add<C>, Div<C>, Mul<C>, MulFloatingPoint, SetOne, SetZero, Sub<C>, Type<C>, Composite<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NumericComposite, RealComposite

    public abstract class AbstractNumericComposite<T extends NumericType<T>,C extends AbstractNumericComposite<T,C>>
extends AbstractComposite<T>
implements NumericType<C>, Iterable<T>
    Abstract base class for a vector of NumericType scalars. It is a NumericType itself, implementing the NumericType algebra as element-wise operations.
    Author:
    Stephan Saalfeld
